'''亞瑟王座'''（'''Arthur's Seat'''） 是一座位於[[蘇格蘭|蘇格蘭]][[愛丁堡|愛丁堡]][[荷里路德公園|荷里路德公園]]的山峰，其高度為{{convert|186|m}}。在山上能夠一覽愛丁堡全景，加上又易於攀登而成為遊客必經之地。[[索爾茲伯里峭壁|索爾茲伯里峭壁]]所在一側較為陡峭，因而也為[[攀岩|攀岩]]愛好者提供了絕佳場所。其頂部有一個小型的山丘堡壘。<ref>{{cite web | url = http://canmore.rcahms.gov.uk/en/site/52561/details/edinburgh+holyrood+park+arthur+s+seat/ | title = Edinburgh, Holyrood Park, Arthur'sSeat | accessdate = 2011-07-05 | archive-date = 2014-09-13 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20140913214549/http://canmore.rcahms.gov.uk/en/site/52561/details/edinburgh+holyrood+park+arthur+s+seat/ | dead-url = no }}</ref>

相傳此地名稱來自[[亞瑟王|亞瑟王]]，這一說法較早記錄見於蘇格蘭的史詩《[[Y_Gododdin|Y Gododdin]]》<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ukhillwalking.com/articles/page.php?id=3381|title=Hill Names and the John Smith Question|date=April 2011|accessdate=2013-12-25|archive-date=2015-07-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150712145132/http://www.ukhillwalking.com/articles/page.php?id=3381|dead-url=no}}</ref>。[[蘇格蘭蓋爾語|蘇格蘭蓋爾語]]中並沒有亞瑟王座的專門稱呼<ref>{{cite book | last1 = Grant | first1 = James | title = Old and New Edinburgh | url = http://www.oldandnewedinburgh.co.uk/volume4/page125.html | accessdate = 2010-10-30 | archive-date = 2020-12-03 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201203013512/http://www.oldandnewedinburgh.co.uk/volume4/page125.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

